                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="75296" author="cliffw" created="Mon, 20 Jan 2014 18:08:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am closing this issue as a non bug. Please reopen if you have further questions/issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73108" author="nedbass" created="Mon, 9 Dec 2013 18:12:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cliff, yes the filesystem is back online after a writeconf. So I guess there is not a bug here, other than poor error reporting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73103" author="cliffw" created="Mon, 9 Dec 2013 18:01:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did the writeconf fix this issue? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73006" author="nedbass" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 18:53:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Minh, we did a writeconf because these are upgraded 1.8 filesystems, and we were advised that a writeconf is needed before going to 2.4. Otherwise clients would not initialize the lmv layer which is needed after DNE landed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72998" author="mdiep" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 17:17:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am curious, why would a writeconf is needed? Unless you need to change the NIDS, or backup/restore.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72996" author="cliffw" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 16:57:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Had a feeling you would say that. I would indeed repeat the writeconf, if there are still issues I would directly examine the ls4-client config log with llog_reader and see what is in there. The writeconf is likely the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72952" author="nedbass" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 00:44:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry Cliff the system is classified.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72951" author="nedbass" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 00:43:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This may have been related to an incomplete writeconf procedure.  Admins are repeating the procedure now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72950" author="cliffw" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 00:43:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you attach the debug log? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72941" author="nedbass" created="Thu, 5 Dec 2013 23:20:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On MGS we get in debug log when client tries to mount:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;MGS fail to handle opc = 501: rc = -2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
